# Plan — AdvertEyes (richness 10/10)

## Status
**READY** — research complete. All 5 gate questions answered by pre-researcher. Core architecture locked; design system confirmed; TomTom Traffic API added; Leaflet Vite fixes documented; Open-Meteo field names corrected. Plan is confirmed and builder-ready.

---

## Demo concept: AdvertEyes Internal Ops Platform

**Full build** (no prototype fallback warranted — richness 10/10 and stack matches Michael's directive exactly).

A production-quality internal web app for an OOH (billboard, truckside, digital DOOH) advertising company. Covers inventory management, campaign booking, live weather/install-risk monitoring, real-time traffic scoring, and RBAC user management — all with a working Node/TS REST backend and a React/TS frontend.

---

## Design system (CONFIRMED — research-derived, not guesses)

**Source:** Outfront Media (dark+bold modern OOH brand), Lamar (clean corporate), Clear Channel (high-contrast B2B). Outfront's dark professional dashboard is the primary reference.

**Mood:** Dark, data-dense, authoritative ops tool. Like a Bloomberg terminal for a $50M outdoor advertising company. Orange accent echoes the bold, visible nature of the medium itself.

**Palette (locked):**
```css
--bg-primary:    #0A0E1A;   /* deep navy, darker than Outfront */
--bg-surface:    #131929;   /* card / sidebar surface */
--bg-elevated:   #1C2540;   /* modals, raised panels */
--border:        #2D3A5A;   /* subtle dividers */
--accent:        #FF6B1A;   /* billboard orange — high-vis industry energy */
--accent-blue:   #3B82F6;   /* DOOH / digital screen blue */
--success:       #22C55E;
--warning:       #EAB308;
--error:         #EF4444;
--text-primary:  #E8EDF5;
--text-muted:    #8A9AC0;
```

**Typography (locked):**
- Display/headings: `Barlow Condensed 700` (compressed headline aesthetic — industry standard in OOH visual identity)
- UI/body: `DM Sans 400/500/600` (clean dashboard readability; NOT Inter per CLAUDE.md)
- Mono/data (KPI numbers, route IDs): `IBM Plex Mono`
- Google Fonts import: `family=Barlow+Condensed:wght@700&family=DM+Sans:wght@400;500;600&family=IBM+Plex+Mono`

**Layout:** Fixed left sidebar (collapsed 64px / expanded 220px) + full-height main area with top bar (user name, role badge, notifications). No mobile breakpoint needed (internal ops tool; 768px min-width sufficient).

