## API route plan

```
POST   /adverteyes/auth/login          { email, password } → { token, user }
GET    /adverteyes/auth/me             → { user, role }

GET    /adverteyes/inventory           ?type=&status=&search=
POST   /adverteyes/inventory           Admin/Sales only
PUT    /adverteyes/inventory/:id       Admin only
DELETE /adverteyes/inventory/:id       Admin only

GET    /adverteyes/clients
POST   /adverteyes/clients             Admin/Sales
GET    /adverteyes/campaigns           ?client_id=&status=
POST   /adverteyes/campaigns           Admin/Sales
PUT    /adverteyes/campaigns/:id

GET    /adverteyes/bookings            ?campaign_id=&unit_id=&from=&to=
POST   /adverteyes/bookings            + conflict check response { conflict: bool, detail: string }
PUT    /adverteyes/bookings/:id
DELETE /adverteyes/bookings/:id

GET    /adverteyes/users               Admin only
POST   /adverteyes/users               Admin only
PUT    /adverteyes/users/:id           Admin only

GET    /adverteyes/weather/:unitId     Open-Meteo proxy, returns parsed forecast + install risk
GET    /adverteyes/traffic/:unitId     TomTom proxy, 15-min cache, returns congestion score

GET    /adverteyes/health              → { ok: true }
```

Both weather and traffic are proxied through the Node backend (keys stay server-side, response is shaped/cached).

